<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="533" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Griscom</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-05-10"><hi rend="italic">May 10,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis informs Mr. Griscom that the New York Tea Association
                            complains that the Japanese Government is granting an annual tea subsidy
                            of 70,000 yen for seven years. Instructs him to investigate, and if
                            report is true to renew earnest representations.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>